consent:
Thank you for taking part in this research. 

 

In this survey you will answer questions about yourself, your financial preferences, your habits, your family, how you envision the future, and more specifically your family mortality history. It should not take you more than 10 minutes to complete. 
The answers you give will be completely confidential and anonymous, as you will only
be identified by your Prolific ID. The final data will be published online but only be accessible in anonymized form. Any reports or publications based on these data will only include aggregated statistics. As such, there will be no way for you to be personally identified based on the answers you give. You can at any time withdraw this consent and stop the questionnaire and/or ask for deletion of your data using your Prolific ID. If you would like to discuss further about anything related to this survey or the research, please contact main investigator Mona Joly (mona.joly@wzb.eu).

 

This research has been approved by the Research Ethics Committee of the Institution carrying out the research, the Berlin Social Science Center (WZB).

 

By clicking the consent button below you confirm to be at least 18 years old, you agree to voluntarily participate, acknowledge that consent can be withdrawn at any moment without prejudice, and accept the data you provide is analyzed and stored by the researcher.

The next questions are about your general habits.



How much effort do you make to look after your health and ensure your safety these days? 

0 is 'no effort at all' and 100 is 'the maximum effort you could make'. - 1

The next two questions are about you and the environment. 
 
How much effort do you make to minimize any negative impact of your lifestyle on the environment?

0 is 'no effort at all' and 100 is 'the maximum effort you could make'. - 1
Q85_1:
How much effort do you make to use environmentally friendly means of transportation for travel (e.g. bike or underground rather than car, train rather than plane)? 
Again, 0 is 'no effort at all' and 100 is 'the maximum effort you could make'. - 1
Q60_1:
The next question is about how you envision the future. 

 

If you made the maximum effort you could make to look after your health and ensure your safety, what do you think the chances would be that you would live to be 75 or more? 

0 is ‘no chance’ and 100 is ‘definitely’. - 1
